        <h1>Your appearance in politics is no dream..</h1>
		<div data-role="collapsible">
		<h3>Step 1</h3>
		<h4>Involve in community activities</h4>
		<p><strong>Tip1:</strong> Start an event/campaign reflecting the issues / policies in School, College and Community on 'My Winks'. Get more 'Votes Up' using your Facebook, Twitter and other social contacts</p>
		<p><strong>Tip2:</strong> Inspire others by briefing your achievements at school, college and other places in 'Message' sections of 'My Winks' </p>
		<p><strong>Tip3:</strong> Writing op-eds to local news papers discussing the issue. Use My winks to seek comments on your op-eds</p>
		</div>
		<div data-role="collapsible">
		<h3>Step 2</h3>
		<h4>Increase your network</h4>
		<p><strong>Tip1:</strong> Invite more people to have them look at your 'Winks'. To be specific local reporters, columnist, political leaders and of course your friend's friends.</p>
			<strong>Tip2:</strong>Use 'My Rep' Feature to get in touch with your representatives.</p>	
		</div>
		<div data-role="collapsible">
		<h3>Step 3</h3>
		<h4>Find Answers for the following</h4>
		<p>3.1 Budgeting - How much funds do you need to run a successful campaign?
		<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Post specific questions and seek suggestions in My Winks
		</p>
		<p>
		<strong>Tip:</strong> Use the My Winks Resource Bundle to find who can answer this,
		</p>
		</p>
		<p>
		3.2 From where can you raise funds?
		<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Start an event in My Winks invite your friends, social contacts, women welfare activists</p>
		
		</p>
		<p>3.3 A crisp Unique Message - How unique your beliefs and actions plan to solve a specific problem?
		<p><strong>Tip:</strong> Start an event/campaign in My Winks tagging the problem and seek Votes Up to self-evaluate your action plans</p>
		</p>
		<p>3.4 Have you identified a team to run your campaign? Start identifying the candidates to do the roles. 
		<p><strong>Campaign Manager -- </strong>The campaign manager is your key, strategic advisor on the campaign, captain of the ship </p>
		<p><strong>Finance Director -- </strong>The Finance director is responsible for helping you plan how you will raise the money you need. The catalyst or acclerator to raise  
funds
</p>
<p>
<strong>Press Secretary --</strong> The press secretary will be a media point of contact and  help you to build your
message and strategic ways to get to the voters
through news stories

</p>
<p><strong>Field Director --</strong> The Field director another important person who oversees voter contact. He or
she will help you make sure you have the votes to win, and that your voters get to the polls

</p>
<p>
<strong>Volunteer Coordinator --</strong> The volunteer coordinator help to recruit volunteers and make sure that they are being used effectively
</p>
<p>      <strong>Scheduler --</strong> The scheduler makes sure that you are going to events and meetings that make strategic sense. While the scheduler will help organize  
logistics, he or she should also have a clear sense of which voters you are targeting

</p>

		</p>
		
